{
  "dhp290:0.1": "Collection of Minor Texts ",
  "dhp290:0.2": "Verses of Dhamma ",
  "dhp290:0.3": "The Scattered Chapter ",
  "dhp290:1": "If by relinquishing limited happiness ",
  "dhp290:2": "one can see abundant happiness, ",
  "dhp290:3": "then one who is wise relinquishes limited happiness ",
  "dhp290:4": "and sees abundant happiness. ",
  "dhp291:1": "By profiting from the suffering of others, ",
  "dhp291:2": "one seeks happiness for oneself; ",
  "dhp291:3": "one who is intimately involved in hostility ",
  "dhp291:4": "is not free from hostility. ",
  "dhp292:1": "They reject what should be done ",
  "dhp292:2": "and do what should not be done; ",
  "dhp292:3": "arrogant and negligent, ",
  "dhp292:4": "their defilements increase. ",
  "dhp293:1": "They have undertaken ",
  "dhp293:2": "continuous mindfulness of the body, ",
  "dhp293:3": "they do not do what should not be done, ",
  "dhp293:4": "and they always do what should be done; ",
  "dhp293:5": "mindful and aware, ",
  "dhp293:6": "their defilements disappear. ",
  "dhp294:1": "Having slain mother and father, ",
  "dhp294:2": "two royal kings, ",
  "dhp294:3": "and a kingdom with its followers, ",
  "dhp294:4": "the brahmin proceeds untroubled. ",
  "dhp295:1": "Having slain mother and father, ",
  "dhp295:2": "two scholar kings, ",
  "dhp295:3": "and a tiger as well, ",
  "dhp295:4": "the brahmin proceeds untroubled. ",
  "dhp296:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp296:2": "the disciples of Gotama ",
  "dhp296:3": "who continuously recollect the Buddha ",
  "dhp296:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp297:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp297:2": "disciples of the Buddha ",
  "dhp297:3": "who continuously recollect the Dhamma ",
  "dhp297:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp298:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp298:2": "the disciples of Gotama ",
  "dhp298:3": "who continuously recollect the Saá¹…gha ",
  "dhp298:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp299:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp299:2": "the disciples of Gotama ",
  "dhp299:3": "who continuously practice mindfulness of the body ",
  "dhp299:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp300:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp300:2": "the disciples of Gotama ",
  "dhp300:3": "who approve of harmlessness ",
  "dhp300:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp301:1": "They always wake up well, ",
  "dhp301:2": "the disciples of Gotama ",
  "dhp301:3": "who approve of self-development ",
  "dhp301:4": "by day and by night. ",
  "dhp302:1": "The renunciant life is difficult and hard to enjoy; ",
  "dhp302:2": "the household life is difficult and hard to endure. ",
  "dhp302:3": "Living with others is suffering, ",
  "dhp302:4": "and travelers also undergo suffering. ",
  "dhp302:5": "Therefore, just as one can choose to not travel, ",
  "dhp302:6": "one can choose to not suffer. ",
  "dhp303:1": "One who has faith and morality, ",
  "dhp303:2": "influence and wealth, ",
  "dhp303:3": "is honored ",
  "dhp303:4": "wherever they are. ",
  "dhp304:1": "Those who are good are visible from afar, ",
  "dhp304:2": "like a Himalayan mountain; ",
  "dhp304:3": "but those who are not good cannot be seen, ",
  "dhp304:4": "like arrows loosed at night. ",
  "dhp305:1": "Sitting alone, sleeping alone, ",
  "dhp305:2": "going alone, never lazy; ",
  "dhp305:3": "training oneself alone, ",
  "dhp305:4": "one can enjoy the forest. "
}